Implementing the Naive Bayes classification algorithm for text classification in Python without external libraries requires careful preprocessing and probability calculation. The training function will calculate the prior probabilities of each class and the likelihood of each word given a class. The prediction function will use these probabilities to determine the most likely class for a new text. The evaluation function will compute the F1 Score to assess the model's performance.

